{
  "title": "Documenting Web Backends Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer provides a comprehensive guide on how to document REST APIs efficiently using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI's automatic API documentation is a standout feature that enhances readability and usability of the APIs.",
    "Docstrings in FastAPI can be used to annotate function parameters, return values, responses, and HTTP requests.",
    "The `include_in_schema` directive controls whether a given tag's documentation is included in the API schema or not.",
    "FastAPI supports OpenAPI 3.0+ specifications for generating interactive documentation and client SDKs in multiple languages.",
    "Documentation can be customized with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript using the `Html` and `Include` tags."
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n\n@app.get('/items/{item_id}')\nasync def read_item(item_id: int, q: str = None):\n    \"\"\" Get an item by its ID \"\""\"\n    if q is None:\n        return {'item': f'Item {item_id}'}\n    return {'item': f'Item {item_id}, query parameter: {q}'}"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for running FastAPI.",
    "FastAPI version 0.68.0 and above support OpenAPI 3.1.x specifications."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Ensure that your development environment has FastAPI installed and correctly configured before proceeding with the tutorial.",
    "While this explainer covers key concepts for documenting APIs using FastAPI, there may be more advanced topics to explore in the official documentation."
  ]
}
